Messages.Content:
right now Godgame is basically “HUD + sanity cube + a whole lot of invisible ECS.”

Here’s a simple path to actually see and test rocks in Godgame without derailing everything.

1. Make a visible rock prefab (authoring)

In Godgame folder:

Create a prefab GG_Rock.

Add:

MeshRenderer + MeshFilter (simple cube/sphere/low-poly rock mesh).

GodgameRockPhysicsAuthoring (or whatever your agent named the rock authoring).

Layer: Rock / ResourceNode.

Collider radius/size matching the mesh.

Raise collision events: on.

ResourceNodeAuthoring (if you have one) or a simple RockResourceAuthoring with Amount=100, Type=Stone or similar.

ShatterProfileAuthoring if that exists yet (or just a basic profile reference).

Make sure this prefab is inside the Godgame SubScene or a dedicated “Godgame_Test” SubScene that gets converted.

2. Drop some rocks into the world

Easiest way (no new systems yet):

Open your Godgame test scene.

Inside the SubScene:

Duplicate GG_Rock prefab a bunch of times.

Scatter them around the sanity cube area.

Give them slightly different Y positions so they can collide and settle.

As soon as the SubScene is open, they’ll bake into ECS with physics components.

3. Add a super simple “poke” mechanic

Since you don’t yet have hand-throw in Godgame, add a tiny “debug nudge” system so you can bump rocks into each other:

// in Godgame/Debug/GodgameRockNudgeSystem.cs
[UpdateInGroup(typeof(SimulationSystemGroup))]
public partial struct GodgameRockNudgeSystem : ISystem
{
    public void OnCreate(ref SystemState state)
    {
        state.RequireForUpdate<GodgamePhysicsBody>(); // or Rock tag
    }

    public void OnUpdate(ref SystemState state)
    {
        if (!UnityEngine.Input.GetKeyDown(KeyCode.N)) // N for Nudge
            return;

        var rand = new Unity.Mathematics.Random(1234u + (uint)System.Environment.TickCount);

        foreach (var (vel, transform) in
                 SystemAPI.Query<RefRW<GodgameVelocity>, RefRO<LocalTransform>>())
        {
            // tiny lateral kick
            float3 dir = math.normalize(new float3(rand.NextFloat(-1,1), 0, rand.NextFloat(-1,1)));
            vel.ValueRW.Linear += dir * 5f; // tweak strength
        }
    }
}

